Some Muslims attended a Christmas service on Saturday in Sabon Tasha, Kaduna state. The church service took place at Christ Evangelical and Life Intervention Ministry. Members of the Islamic Movement in Nigeria (IMN), popularly known as Shiites, were also present at the church. According to NAN, the church played host to 525 Muslims as part of efforts to strengthen religious tolerance and Christian-Muslim relationship. Abdullahi Rabo, district head of Kurmin-Mashi, and Ahmad Rabo, Tijjaniya Imam, also presented a gift to Yuhana Buru, general overseer of the church. Some of the Muslim attendees also joined the Christians in a dance. See pictures below. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-643544" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Screenshot_20211225-174436.png" alt="" width="600" height="381" /> <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-643545" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Screenshot_20211225-174421.png" alt="" width="600" height="643" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-643546" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/Screenshot_20211225-174407.png" alt="" width="600" height="515" />
